{
    "word": "Diction",
    "definitions": [
        "Choice of words for the expression of ideas; the construction, disposition, and application of words in discourse, with regard to clearness, accuracy, variety, etc.; mode of expression; language; as, the diction of Chaucer's poems."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "His diction blazes up into a sudden explosion of prophetic grandeur."
    ],
    "etymology": "[L. dicto a saying, a word, fr. dicere, dictum, to say; akin to dicare to proclaim, and to E. teach, token: cf. F. diction. See Teach, and cf. Benison, Dedicate, Index, Judge, Preach, Vengeance.]"
}